  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_150",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_150"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_116"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Of course, we see the geopolitical situation. We see what Russia is doing. Russia is destroying; Europe helps â Europe helps with development solidarity. Russia uses energy to blackmail you; the EU installs solar panels and connects the energy centres. Russia divides; the EU unites.\nAnd â that I saw as an election observer â the Moldovans are strong. They defend their democracy, and we have to help them there as well.\nOne more thing: there is beautiful soil there, they are great agriculture, wine we know, and also wonderful culture. It's always great to listen to Moldovan singers, like Valentina NaforniÈa. If she is in Vienna State Opera, in any other opera, please go listen to her, she's wonderful, like many others as well."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-10T20:56:26"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_110",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "participant_110"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#isAffiliatedWith": [
